      "text": "My repo: YOUR-USERNAME/YOUR-REPO\n\nI have a private \"AI Hub\" that shows markdown files from a GitHub repo as cards.\nPlease create my first card so I can see it appear and actually use it.\n\nSetup:\n- My private GitHub repo: the one I named at the very top of this prompt.\n- A GitHub token (Contents read + write) is in the file gh-token.txt in this folder.\n  Use it ONLY for git authentication. Never print it, never commit it.\n- The Hub displays markdown files from the repo's content/ folder. The category must be\n  exactly tools or library (lowercase).\n\nIMPORTANT. How to do it: use plain git over HTTPS inside your own sandbox/workspace.\nThe sandbox CAN reach github.com via git (clone / commit / push). Do NOT use the GitHub\nREST API (api.github.com is blocked), do NOT use the browser, and do NOT use computer-use\nor a terminal on my machine.\n\nSteps:\n1. Read the token from gh-token.txt.\n2. git clone https://x-access-token:<TOKEN>@github.com/<my-repo>.git into a temp folder,\n   where <my-repo> is the repo I named at the top.\n3. Create ONE card in content/ (top level), with frontmatter (title, emoji, category, updated = today):\n\n   file content/hub-cheat-sheet.md\n   ---\n   title: Hub Cheat-Sheet\n   emoji: 🗺️\n   category: library\n   updated: <today>\n   ---\n   A short, practical reference I keep. Cover, in plain language:\n   - What a card is: a .md file in content/ with frontmatter (title, emoji, category, updated).\n   - The two categories: tools = things my AI runs or produces for me; library = saved\n     references, prompts, DNA.\n   - That a scheduled task can automatically write its result as a card to my Hub.\n   - How to add an idea on the Ideas board, and that finished ideas become Wins.\n\n   Then, in the SAME card, add a section titled \"## What's next: starter ideas\".\n   Build it from what I ALREADY have: take stock of my setup (list my installed skills, my plugins,\n   and my existing scheduled tasks using your tools, and read any DNA or context files in this folder).\n   Then give me 6 to 8 concrete, pick-and-build-able ideas, one line each, focused on turning what I\n   already run into Hub cards: for each scheduled task or skill I already have, how it could write a\n   useful card to my Hub; plus a couple of new scheduled tasks worth adding, tailored to my real work\n   and tools. Ground every suggestion in something real you found about me. If I have nothing set up yet\n   and no context, fall back to strong general ideas (a daily morning briefing, an inbox-triage summary,\n   a weekly metrics snapshot, a competitor scan, a meeting recap, an expense/receipt log, a weekly\n   learning digest, fresh content ideas).\n\n4. git add, commit, and push to main (token in the remote URL).\n\nThen I'll reload my Hub. The card appears under Library."
